@startuml
title CameraHandler - Class Diagram (RealSense / USB Camera)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class CameraHandler {
  +is_real_sense: bool
  +camera_no: str
  +warmup_frames: int

  -pipeline: rs.pipeline
  -cap: cv2.VideoCapture
  -latest_frame: np.ndarray
  -frame_lock: threading.Lock
  -is_running: bool
  -capture_thread: threading.Thread
  -frame_count: int

  --
  +__init__(is_real_sense=True, camera_no="...", warmup_frames=30)
  -_initialize_camera()
  -_init_realsense()
  -_init_usb_camera()
  -_capture_loop()

  +start_capture()
  +get_frame(): np.ndarray
  +get_latest_frame_threaded(): np.ndarray
  +get_frame_count(): int
  +is_ready(): bool
  +stop()
  +__enter__()
  +__exit__(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb)
  +__del__()
}

class "rs.pipeline" as RSPipeline
class "rs.config" as RSConfig
class "cv2.VideoCapture" as CVCap
class "numpy.ndarray" as NDArray
class "threading.Thread" as Thd
class "threading.Lock" as Lck

CameraHandler --> RSPipeline : uses when is_real_sense
CameraHandler --> RSConfig : config on init
CameraHandler --> CVCap : uses when USB
CameraHandler --> Thd : capture_thread
CameraHandler --> Lck : frame_lock
CameraHandler --> NDArray : latest_frame\n(BGR uint8 HxWx3)

note right of CameraHandler
Frame format:
- type: numpy.ndarray
- shape: (H, W, 3) e.g. (1080, 1920, 3)
- dtype: uint8
- channel: BGR
end note

@enduml
